Hereâ€™s a pure-CLI sequence using GitHub CLI (gh) to create a PR and merge it.

Replace placeholders like feature/my-change, commit messages, and branch names as needed.

Install & login (first time only)

sudo apt update && sudo apt install -y gh
gh auth login


From your repo, update main

git checkout main
git pull origin main


Create a feature branch

git checkout -b feature/my-change


Make changes (example creates/edits a file)

nano key_value_pairs.py


Stage & commit

git add -A
git commit -m "Add key_value_pairs.py"


Push the branch to GitHub

git push -u origin feature/my-change


Create the PR (into main)

gh pr create --base main --head feature/my-change --title "Add key_value_pairs.py" --body "Adds key-value example file."


(Optional) Check PR status

gh pr status


Merge the PR (pick ONE style)

# Merge commit:
gh pr merge feature/my-change --merge

# OR squash & merge (common):
gh pr merge feature/my-change --squash --delete-branch

# OR rebase & merge:
gh pr merge feature/my-change --rebase --delete-branch


Sync local main

git checkout main
git pull origin main


(Optional) Clean up local branch

git branch -d feature/my-change
